    "actor_description": "I stop negotiating with myself. The noise falls back and the next step comes forward-simple, doable. My attention narrows until it has edges; everything irrelevant goes slightly dim. Breath steadies. Jaw tightens once, then settles. I can feel my body choosing efficiency: smaller movements, cleaner timing, no wasted gestures. The fear doesn't have to be gone; it just doesn't get a vote. I pick the line I'm going to walk and start walking it.",
    "description_text": "{actor} becomes precise. Their gaze fixes and stops wandering. Movements shorten-hands doing only what they need to, nothing ornamental. The set of their mouth hardens into intent, and they start acting in a straight line, as if they've already decided what matters and everything else can wait.",
